EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" />
Thank you for attending our recent International Baccalaureate (IB) Open Evening. We hope you found the evening informative and inspiring as well as a chance to get a feel for the program by SACS students who are currently enrolled.
Whatever academic choice you feel is right for your family, SACS is here as a strong support base through your childs important - and final - years of school. Both the IB and HSC at SACS are taught by passionate staff who are determined to ensure students are well-equipped both academically and socially to enter the post-school world.
The next step in the process of selecting an academic direction for Year 11 and 12 is to come along to the IB/HSC subject information night next term. After this, your child will be able to submit an online subject selection form indicating if they will choose to undertake the IB. Your family will receive in invite to the subject information night when school returns next term.
If you have any questions regarding the IB, please feel free to contact Mrs Sharon Munro, our IB Cooordinator on 9286 9528 or via email. You will also find the IB information booklet (handed out at the event) attached to this email.
You can also find more IB information on our website.
Regards,
Robyn
